4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT GENERALLY REVISING PUBLIC AND SCHOOL LIBRARY
5 STANDARDS; PROHIBITING THE EXCLUSION OF A BOOK OR OTHER RESOURCE FROM A SCHOOL
6 LIBRARY FOR CERTAIN REASONS; REQUIRING SCHOOL DISTRICT TRUSTEES TO ADOPT A POLICY
7 AND PROCEDURES TO OBJECT TO A BOOK OR OTHER RESOURCE INCLUDED IN A SCHOOL
8 LIBRARY; PROHIBITING A PUBLIC LIBRARY FROM BANNING OR RESTRICTING ACCESS TO A BOOK
9 OR OTHER RESOURCE BASED ON THE VIEWPOINT OF THAT BOOK OR RESOURCE; REQUIRING A
10 LIBRARY BOARD OF TRUSTEES TO ADOPT A POLICY REGARDING THE MATERIALS IN A PUBLIC
11 LIBRARY'S COLLECTION; AMENDING SECTIONS 20-7-204 AND 22-1-302, MCA; AND PROVIDING AN
12 EFFECTIVE DATE.”
13
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
15
16 Section 1. Section 20-7-204, MCA, is amended to read:
17 "20-7-204. School library book selection. (1) School library books shall must be selected in
18 accordance with the requirements of this section by the district superintendent or a principal if there is no district
19 superintendent, subject to the approval of the trustees. In districts not employing a superintendent or principal,
20 the trustees shall select the school library books on the basis of recommendations of the county
21 superintendent.
22 (2) The books, materials, services, and resources provided in a school library must be provided for
23 the interest, information, and instructional support of the students and school personnel who are served by the
24 school library.
25 (3) A book or other resource may not be excluded from a school library solely because of the
26 origin, background, or views of the individual who created the book or other resource. A book or other resource
27 may not be excluded from the school library catalog because of partisan, ideological, or religious disapproval."
28
