1 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Objection to school library material -- process required. (1) The
2 trustees of a school district shall develop and implement a policy and procedures to review objections to books
3 or other resources in the school library.
4 (2) The policy and procedures developed pursuant to this section must:
5 (a) establish a uniform process to submit an objection to materials in a school library by a student
6 enrolled at the school served by the school library, a parent or guardian of a student enrolled at the school
7 served by the school library, or a school staff member employed at the school served by the school library;
8 (b) require materials under review due to an objection to remain available for use by students and
9 school staff members until the review process has concluded; and
10 (c) establish a reasonable timeline to conduct and conclude the review process in a timely manner.
11 (3) On completion of a library material challenge or reconsideration process pursuant to the policy
12 adopted under this section, the school district trustees shall submit a report of the challenge to the
13 superintendent of public instruction with the following information:
14 (a) the title, author, and other relevant identifying information about the material being challenged;
15 (b) the date, time, and location of any public hearing that was held related to the challenge,
16 including minutes or transcripts;
17 (c) the result of the challenge or reconsideration request; and
18 (d) a person who may be contacted by the superintendent of public instruction for questions or
19 FOLLOWUP.
20
21 Section 3. Section 22-1-302, MCA, is amended to read:
22 "22-1-302. Purpose. (1) It is the purpose of this part to encourage the establishment, adequate
23 financing, and effective administration of free public libraries in this state to give the people of Montana the
24 fullest opportunity to enrich and inform themselves through reading.
25 (2) In furtherance of this purpose, a public library may not ban, remove, or otherwise restrict
26 access to a book or other material based solely on the viewpoint of the book or other material or the messages,
27 ideas, or opinions conveyed by the book or other material."
