1 NEW SECTION. Section 4. Library materials policy -- reporting requirement. (1) The board of
2 trustees for a public library shall adopt a policy that establishes procedures for the selection of, challenges to,
3 and reconsideration of library materials pursuant to this section. The policy must comply with the requirements
4 of 22-1-302(2).
5 (2) The policy must provide that the procedures for the selection and reconsideration of library
6 materials must be administered by the chief librarian.
7 (3) The policy for the selection of library materials must provide that the chief librarian may decline
8 to purchase, lend, or make available on a library shelf and that the chief librarian may remove or restrict access
9 to books or other materials for:
10 (a) practical reasons, including but not limited to shelf space limitations, rare or antiquarian status,
11 damage, or obsolescence;
12 (b) legitimate pedagogical concerns, including but not limited to the appropriateness of potentially
13 sensitive topics for the library's intended audience, or the selection of books and materials for a curated
14 collection; or
15 (c) compliance with state or federal law.
16 (4) (a) The policy must provide that a challenge to a library material must be administered by the
17 chief librarian.
18 (b) On completion of a library material challenge or reconsideration process pursuant to the policy
19 adopted under this section, the library board of trustees shall submit a report of the challenge to the state
20 librarian with the following information:
21 (i) the title, author, and other relevant identifying information about the material being challenged;
22 (ii) the date, time, and location of any public hearing that was held related to the challenge,
23 including minutes or transcripts;
24 (iii) the result of the challenge or reconsideration request; and
25 (iv) a person who may be contacted by the state librarian for questions or followup.
26 (5) If the library board of trustees adopts a written policy consistent with this section, an employee
27 of the public library may not be dismissed, suspended, disciplined, demoted, reassigned, transferred, or
28 otherwise retaliated against for performing the employee's job duties consistent with the written policy.
